		<category><![CDATA[steampunk]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://clockworktwist.com/?p=2396</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Hello, lovelies!  Sorry about stepping out like that.  Right after I put this blog on pause, the chaos in my life intensified exponentially.  Typical, right?  Not to whine, and not to go into too much detail, I had a failed surgery, then a much better one that fixed the problem, lost two dear friends suddenly and [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="attachment_2397" style="width: 670px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.amazon.com/Alice-Wonderland-Mia-Wasikowska/dp/B003QTUQGU/" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-2397" class="wp-image-2397 size-full" src="http://clockworktwist.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/29.jpg" alt="" width="660" height="350" srcset="https://clockworktwist.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/29.jpg 660w, https://clockworktwist.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/29-300x159.jpg 300w, https://clockworktwist.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/29-618x327.jpg 618w" sizes="(max-width: 660px) 100vw, 660px" /></a><p id="caption-attachment-2397" class="wp-caption-text">White Rabbit concept art by michael kutsche © Disney Enterprises Inc</p></div>
<p>Hello, lovelies!  Sorry about stepping out like that.  Right after I put this blog on pause, the chaos in my life intensified exponentially.  Typical, right?  Not to whine, and not to go into too much detail, I had a failed surgery, then a much better one that fixed the problem, lost two dear friends suddenly and in the space of a week, lost my job, got another job and then lost that very quickly.  When I paused the blog, I was only expecting the surgery part, not any of the rest.  Now that things have calmed down somewhat, I&#8217;m starting to get my feet back under me.  My family and I went to the circus just for the hell of it, went to see our favorite comedian preform, and I went to see Guardians of the Galaxy a few times too.  It&#8217;s funny how sometimes even the silliest and more trivial things can trigger true healing, isn&#8217;t it?  And so, here I am.  Still a bit dizzy, but back in the world!  lol</p>
<p>In the meantime, all things Twist have been progressing nicely.  Honestly, Twist was the only thing I wanted to work on through all of my troubles.  It was just a nice, cozy place to be.  Book 3 is in final edits as we speak, and I&#8217;m nearly finished with the cover design!  I&#8217;m so excited to show you all!  I&#8217;ll have a preview of the cover up soon, along with the first 3 chapters, as usual.  Stay tuned!</p>
<p><a href="http://jefferysimian.wordpress.com/" target="_blank">Jeffery</a> is also starting to get some attention as well, which pleases me greatly.  The 11th chapter of his little story will go live on Thursday, and <a href="http://jefferysimian.wordpress.com/journal-entries/" target="_blank">all the previous chapters</a> are still available to enjoy.  I&#8217;m going to leave that book on his blog indefinitely, as a forever freebie, just for you.  But I&#8217;ll also be releasing it as an eBook and paperback as well, at the lowest price The Great And Powerful Amazon will allow.</p>
<p>Other than all of that, I discovered something magical!  Have you ever used <a href="http://ifttt.com/">IFTTT</a>?  It&#8217;s amazing.  I&#8217;m probably going to do a whole blog post about it soon, and how I&#8217;m using it&#8217;s awesome might to my own ends.  In the meantime, check out my <a href="http://cwtwist.tumblr.com/" target="_blank">Tumblr</a>, <a href="http://twitter.com/cwtwist" target="_blank">Twitter</a>, and <a href="http://www.facebook.com/CWTwist" target="_blank">Facebook</a> for daily visual treats.  And that&#8217;s all I&#8217;ll say for now&#8230;</p>
<p>Lastly, I&#8217;d like to mention that I&#8217;m going to be changing things up a little around here.  You might see less pure steampunk things in the future.  Following a single theme was very helpful for me as I learned the art of blogging and social mediaing, but now it&#8217;s becoming restrictive.  There&#8217;s plenty of beauty and great stories in the world, outside of one genre.  I&#8217;ll still be sharing lots of Victorian goodies and as many pretty pocket watches as I can find, but there were be less steamy items as well.</p>
<p>Thanks for sticking around, while I dealt with my issues.  You guys are the best!</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
